        <h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a></a>Sarita Udyan</h3>
        <p>Locals love to picnic in Sarita Udyan, and it’s conveniently situated next to a deer park, another must-visit attraction. It captivates audiences of all ages, from children to adults.</p>
        <h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a></a>Craftsmen’s Village</h3>
        <p>Hundreds of tourists and shoppers flock to Gandhinagar’s Craftsmen’s Village every day, which is known for its Bandhani sarees and is situated beside the Sabarmati river. Using vibrantly colored wooden printing blocks, artisans hand-print sarees and garments. The clothes are inexpensive and expertly made here.</p>

        <h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a></a>Indroda Dinosaur &amp; Fossil Park</h3>

        <p>The Indroda Dinosaur &amp; Fossil Park is a magnificent 400-hectare site that lies on the banks of the River Sabarmati. The park is home to the skeletons of massive creatures like blue whales, and it is also the world’s second-largest dinosaur-egg hatchery! In addition to the camping facilities, the park’s grounds have a large botanical garden, an amphitheater, and an interpretation center.</p>

        <h3 class="wp-block-heading"><a></a>Sant Sarovar Dam</h3>

        <p>The Sant Sarovar Dam, constructed to divert the dangerous currents of the River Sabarmati, is a popular Gandhinagar picnic spot. Indulge in a refreshing plunge in the sacred river and have a memorable weekend with your loved ones at this popular spot, which is conveniently located near the Sarita Garden. During the monsoons, be cautious since the ground can become very wet and the currents can be quite violent.</p>

